{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bfb1a8f1-8427-4adb-af3e-8596cac8a719","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the key problem:\n\n**Dropped framework support:** MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET Core targets. Your project targets `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0`, both of which are **unsupported** in MSTest v3. Only `net462` (.NET Framework 4.6.2+) remains compatible.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n1. Update your TFMs — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. Replace the two package references (`MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter`) with the single consolidated **`MSTest`** package (v3.x).\n\n**Other MSTest v3 breaking changes to watch for:**\n- Default `ClassCleanupBehavior` changed to `EndOfClass` (was `EndOfAssembly`).\n- Some previously obsolete APIs were removed.\n- `Assert.AreEqual`/`AreNotEqual` for `double`/`float` with a delta now fail if delta is `NaN` or negative.\n\nI'd recommend updating your target frameworks first, then bumping to MSTest v3.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10bc1149-fd4c-4a37-abc3-828cd30d5c66","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project that targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `net462` — .NET Framework 4.6.2 is the minimum supported .NET Framework version in MSTest v3, so this should still be supported.\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` — This is EOL and MSTest v3 dropped support for .NET Core 3.1.\n   - `net5.0` — This is also EOL and MSTest v3 dropped support for .NET 5.0.\n\nSo the user will run into compatibility issues with both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` since MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0 or later for .NET Core/.NET versions.\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: MSTest v3 also consolidated its packages, moving away from separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.\n\n3. **Breaking changes**: There are some behavioral and API changes in v3 worth mentioning—like the `ClassCleanupBehavior` default changing, removal of obsolete APIs, and some Assert modifications.\n\nI should give a concise but practical answer that addresses the compatibility issue and these key changes.","outputTokens":708,"requestId":"480A:1E8C:3C1A35:4493A4:69FBFCE4"},"id":"7aa2235b-4d8c-4c6e-b264-d5ae9aad2320","timestamp":"2026-05-07T02:46:11.298Z","parentId":"bcc1f7e9-16b9-483c-96f6-fe2d670ce6c9"}
